If you missed our live here you go! 

As requested, another impromptu casual Q&A format this week! So many random questions but I hope this is helpful. 

As always, thank you for your time and for trusting me as your trainer. 

Sending you so much love!!!

#kelseywells #pwr #sweatchallenge #q&a #kelseywellspwr

node.text:
Do you ever feel yourself growing discouraged when asking yourself (or me) this question?? 

I know this isn’t the answer you are looking for when you ask your trainer this, but THIS MATTERS THE MOST! 

The most the most the most. 

Please. 

PLEASE consider #redefiningfitness for yourself and looking at exercise as something other than changing the way your body looks.❤️🙏🏼

ILYSM

node.text:
Here is our live Q&A from yesterday’s #sweatchallenge #motivationmonday !! 

Is it more important to focus on small habits than dramatic changes? 

What if my family and friends don’t 
agree with or support my efforts? 

How can I stay motivated when I’m sick or injured and can’t train?

How can I get my loved one to finally start taking care of their health?

How can I switch my mindset from training for aesthetics to training for strength? 

ILYSM

I am so grateful for you! I am so grateful for your trust and to be your trainer ❤️🙏🏼

#sweatchallenge Motivation Monday #3 coming off of the holiday weekend I wanted to talk all things nutrition! 

How I currently eat

How I USED to eat

How I made the switch 

How YOU can SUCCESSFULLY make life-long changes to fuel your body better and make a healthier diet your new NORMAL 

Food guilt 

The best way of eating for YOU 

SOOO much in here that I covered quite quickly but I hope this helps. Biggest takeaway: 

Fitness and nutrition go hand in hand, but so do physical health and MENTAL HEALTH. Your MENTAL relationship with food matters MOST. Start there. 

NOTHING you could have eaten is as unhealthy for you as feeling like you are LESS THAN for eating it. 

Always always reach out for help if needed. 

ILYSM ❤️🙏🏼

#kelseywellspwr #redefinefitness #pwr #nutrition #diet #healthymind

node.text:
#SWEATCHALLENGE MOTIVATION MONDAY 2! 

I tried to write out the highlights of what I was trying to say, so if the video feels scattered here you go:

LIFE rewards EFFORT 

PROGRESS is the product of PERSEVERANCE 
And it is dictated by Your DIRECTION— NOT your level of perfection 

STOP COMPARING YOURSELF to anyone else. 

YOU carry and have faced unique struggles, burdens, heartaches, life quakes. 

The life you have lived and all that you have been through is YOURS and yours alone. 

If anyone else in this world was wearing your EXACT shoes, who is to say they could have or would have done it better than you? 

Regardless what mistakes you think you’ve made or what regrets you’ve collected along your way— YOU CANNOT GO BACK. 
You cannot change the past. 
But you CAN change how you look back at your life and the EFFORT you put in TODAY. 

You are in complete control of your actions and perspective and EFFORT right now, today. 

So what about when you’re struggling? 
What about the times in life when you feel you’re not “on your A game” or “giving your best effort”? 

YOUR STRUGGLES ARE SACRED.
Your struggles are something you never need to be ashamed of. 

I was asked “what are you most proud of”— and it isn’t the moments I’ve stepped on stage. Magazine cover shoots or bench hops for days or any career opportunity or accolade.

It is the quiet moments no one has seen 
It is the hours I’ve spent on my knees 
My darkest nights simply fighting to be—

My STRUGGLES have made me who I am. 

It’s taken me years to understand that when I am struggling— I need to meet myself with GRACE and without judgment. Because THAT effort is most pivotal and important. So to each of you who reached out struggling— BE SO PROUD OF YOURSELF AMIDST YOUR STRUGGLES. 

Happy WEEK 2 of the sweat challenge my friend. ILYSM 🤗❤️🤗❤️🤗

node.title: YOUR BEST EFFORT • Your STRUGGLES are SACRED

Did this resonate in any way? 
Do you accept my simple challenge?

To be honest, sometimes I doubt my ability to articulate the things I want to share with you, especially when I feel I really need to say them.

But I did my best. I always have in this space, and (even if I feel nervous or terrified lol) I always will.💛

Day one of another #sweatchallenge is here! I wanted to focus today on two things, AND CHALLENGE YOU!!!!

⚡️The MOTIVE for your MOVEMENT MATTERS. Make your BASELINE GOAL to  use this challenge and your exercise to care for your HEALTH. 

⚡️Where you are RIGHT NOW is perfect. Meet yourself there. Begin to celebrate your body and your health not only focus on changing it. You have not failed. You cannot fail. 

⚡️PWR CHALLENGE: SET YOUR INTENTION AS YOU BEGIN EVERY SINGLE WORKOUT: 

I am exercising today to CARE FOR MY BODY! 
I am doing this session to CELEBRATE my body!
I start my workout right now full of GRATITUDE for my body! 
The fact that I am in good enough health to do this workout is an immense blessing. 

LMK if you accept this challenge!!!

You got this. I got you. 

ILYSM 

#sweat #kelseywells #pwr #fitnesschallenge #mindfulness #mindfulmovement #redefinefitness #ilysm #kelseywellspwr #trainer #fittip

node.text:
Let’s normalize STRUGGLING. 

Let’s dismantle the inaccurate assumption that if someone is happy and thriving, they never struggle.

EVERYONE has tough times. 
EVERYONE experiences ups and downs. 

When and why did we start believing there is something WRONG with that? 

I began THRIVING in my life when I finally let burn the belief that I was never supposed to be sad, or feel anxiety, or grieve, or lose my patience, or feel insecure. 

JOY and heartbreak are not mutually exclusive. 

BEING IN LOVE WITH YOUR LIFE starts with accepting ALL of it. 

As always, remember that ALL of your thoughts and feelings are valid, but YOU are not your thoughts and feelings. 

Focus on the things you CAN control: your attitude + your actions

Keep trying. Keep surviving. Keep THRIVING. 

Don’t be so hard on yourself.❤️

⚡️STOP comparing yourself to others

Reach out to her if you have any questions about her journey or comment below! 

THIS COMMUNITY IS THE BEST!!!!🌎🙌🏼❤️

I am SO stoked to have my new program Low Impact Strength With Kelsey be a part of SWEAT’s campaign to help you MOVE AGAIN! 

Sweat launched three other Beginner level programs alongside mine, from three other POWERFUL, incredible trainers.

“WHY did you create Low Impact Strength With Kelsey? What made you decide to do it?”

This question came through in the Q&A box earlier today, and maybe it was the capitalized *WHY* — but this question stuck with me all day. 

There are many reasons— I had already just finished explaining ‘why’ when she asked. 

But when I got in the car after my PWR session today, it it hit me square in the chest. How I needed to answer her. What I wish I would have said the second she asked. 

THIS is it. THIS is my why. 

Always has been. 

I love you guys so SO much. 

YOU deserve this.

node.text:
GUYS MEDITATING IS THE BOMB!!

Do you meditate? Why or why not?? 

I have shared for years how Meditation is the second greatest tool I have personally used to change my life, empower myself, and care for my overall HEALTH. 

For World Meditation Day, I wanted to talk about the top three assumptions I previously held about meditating that prevented me back from implementing meditation in my life. 

I also touched on just some of the biggest benefits that I have personally seen in my life from my meditation practice: 

- Stress relief 
- Managing/feeling through my anxiety 
- MORE POSITIVE OUTLOOK
- Self-Awareness 
- Better sleep 

I hope this helps! I love meditation. I am so damn grateful for it.

node.text:
“HOW DO YOU ALWAYS STAY MOTIVATED?” 

I can’t count the number of times I’m asked this, and the answer is I absolutely don’t— not in the traditional sense that is. 

ACTION CREATES MOTIVATION! 

Because the MOTIVE for my movement is so clear and important to me, I CHOOSE to exercise DISCIPLINE instead of waiting around to feel motivation. 

Funny thing is, the more you do that, the more motivated you will start to feel 😏🤗

GET UP AND DO SOMETHING TO CARE FOR YOUR HEALTH TODAY!! 

Ilsym ❤️

#kelseywells #redefinefitness #pwr #motivation #trainer #fitness

node.text:
Do you agree? Exercise CAN be SUCH A POWERFUL tool to care for our mental health, but it can also actually be detrimental in certain circumstances. 

The MOTIVE for your movement MATTERS. 

I challenged you a few weeks ago to get super INTENTIONAL about every single one of your PWR sessions— how? 

By literally taking a moment prior to each and every workout to SET INTENTIONS FOR THAT WORKOUT. 

⚡️ I am exercising to care for my body and my health! 

⚡️I am GRATEFUL to be healthy enough to exercise right now. 

⚡️My body is STRONG and POWERFUL. I AM strong and powerful! 

During your session? BE PRESENT IN YOUR BODY! 

Shut out distractions and dismantle any self-depreciating thoughts. 

Feel your heart beating. Connect to your muscles working. Focus on your breath. 

The after your session? Thank your body— and be proud of yourself for choosing to be disciplined, and prioritizing yourself and your health. 

If you’ve tried any of the above, how do you feel? Do you recognize the difference? 

ILYSM❤️🙏🏼

#kelseywells #redefiningfitness #redefinefitness #selflove

node.text:
Do you ever feel yourself growing discouraged when asking yourself (or me) this question?? 

I know this isn’t the answer you are looking for when you ask your trainer this, but THIS MATTERS THE MOST! 

The most the most the most. 

Please. 

PLEASE consider #redefiningfitness for yourself and looking at exercise as something other than changing the way your body looks.❤️🙏🏼

ILYSM

node.text:
SWIPE and read what @mikelyn_delaine has to say about her #pwrprogress journey! So proud of you mama and amen— MENTAL HEALTH MATTERS!❤️🙌🏼⚡️

If you are unsure where to start of your journey, I will meet you WHEREVER you are at— 

post partum? #pwrpostpregnancy 

In the gym or wanting to be? #PWR 

Training from home? #pwrathome 

Don’t have ANY equipment? #pwrzeroequipment 

Needing a very gentle start with short sessions and NO jumping? Low Impact Strength with Kelsey is perfect for you! 

All available in the sweat app ❤️

Here is our live Q&A from yesterday’s #sweatchallenge #motivationmonday !! 

Is it more important to focus on small habits than dramatic changes? 

What if my family and friends don’t 
agree with or support my efforts? 

How can I stay motivated when I’m sick or injured and can’t train?

How can I get my loved one to finally start taking care of their health?

How can I switch my mindset from training for aesthetics to training for strength? 

ILYSM

I am so grateful for you! I am so grateful for your trust and to be your trainer ❤️🙏🏼

node.text:
Snaps from the weekend— the last photo tho🌪🤪

I do not live to workout. 
I workout to live my healthiest, happiest life! 

When I finally began exercising as a tool for self-empowerment (which began by simply exercising to help myself and take care of my body instead to change or “fix” my body)— I set myself free. 

It doesn’t need to be hours a day. 

I started as a new mama, drowning in post-natal anxiety, working full-time as a stay-at-home mom. 

Now, even as a fitness professional, I choose do not workout excessively. I use my own programming and I do 3-5 PWR sessions each week. 

My point is: I understand that implementing exercise as a regular part of your life can be SO OVERWHELMING, but I promise you, IT IS SO WORTH IT. 

Every day, choose to do one thing to invest in caring for yourself and your health. 

Start today. Take it one day at a time. 

And watch as the days go by and that investment returns to you and your loved ones ten fold. 

If you’re not sure where to start? I GOT YOU: 

PWR 
PWR at Home 
PWR Zero Equipment 
PWR Post-Pregnancy 
Low Impact Strength With Kelsey

Wherever you’re at, let me meet you there.🤗

ILYSM
